<section class="sec bg-white relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-10 text-center">2-in-1 Hybrid <span class="text-brandOrange">FAQ</span></h2>
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is a 2-in-1 hybrid charger?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">A 2-in-1 hybrid charger combines a wall AC charger and a portable power bank in a single device. Plug it into the wall to charge your phone directly, then unplug and use it as a power bank on the go. It replaces two devices with one and uses GaN technology for compact size.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Can a 2-in-1 hybrid charger charge a laptop?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. The WOP69 model delivers 67W PD output, sufficient to charge most USB-C laptops including MacBook Air, Dell XPS 13, and many ultrabooks at full speed. The WOP67 at 45W charges 13-inch MacBooks and lighter laptops at full speed, and tops up 16-inch MacBook Pro at reduced rate.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the MOQ for 2-in-1 hybrid charger OEM?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">MOQ starts at 500 units for standard ODM models with custom logo printing. Custom OEM with tooling: 1,000-2,000 units. Sample turnaround: 3-7 days for standard, 10-15 days for custom.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the difference between WOP69 and WOP67?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">WOP69 is the flagship: 67W GaN PD output, 15000mAh capacity, retractable USB-C cable, global plug options. WOP67 is the compact option: 45W PD, 10000mAh, built-in fixed cable. WOP69 suits laptop users and premium retail; WOP67 fits phone-first travel and corporate gift programs.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Can you take a 2-in-1 hybrid charger on a plane?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. All 9 WOWOHCOOL 2-in-1 models are under 100Wh — the IATA limit for carry-on lithium batteries without airline pre-approval. The largest model (WOP69, 15000mAh) is only 55.5Wh. UN38.3 certified with complete MSDS documentation for international air freight.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Is a power bank with wall charger better than a regular power bank?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">For travelers and minimalist users, yes. A 2-in-1 hybrid replaces both a wall charger and a power bank, reducing carry weight by 30-40% and simplifying packing. For brands, it commands 40-60% higher MSRP than a standalone power bank of the same capacity, with one SKU instead of two.</p>
